Arch:
- a map that lets us encode a tree using key name hierarchy.
  e.g. conf, conf.CpuInfo, conf.CpuInfo.FmtString ...

- use map to store config
- use map to store data

- registers to calc data

- seperate out storing data and updating the UI

Features:
- add per process cpu, swap usage indicators
- add Notify() in UI
- add colors to UI
- network data rates
- open netw sockets, per process net usage (bpf ?)
